value: Breeds on the coast of Alaska from the delta of the Yukon to Point Barrow. Winters on both coasts of America from Washington and North Carolina to Peru and Venezuela, including Cuba, Hispaniola and Trinidad.

value: Coastal, hilly sedge–dwarf tundra, generally near water (breeding); mudflats, beaches, shores of shallow lakes and ponds, and flooded fields, in winter primarily on tidal mudflats (nonbreeding).
